      "writtenOn": "2019-06-11T13:58:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There\u0027s subtle things going on there. The CTRL_BREAK_EVENT event is sent to the process group, and the process group is associated to a console. The bot used CREATE_NEW_PROCESS_GROUP to separate the child process from run_isolated, but this was seen as not being enough, so eventually I switched to CREATE_NEW_CONSOLE.\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/desktop/ProcThread/process-creation-flags\n\nThe CTRL_C_EVENT is sent to a process. Historically in the Swarming bot, I\u0027ve sent CTRL_BREAK_EVENT because I wanted all the processes to die. :) I\u0027m fine with revisiting this decision.",
